We are thrilled to add the brilliant rebel leader and pilot of the Ghost to the Washington State Toy Show in PUYALLUP on April 1st and 2nd.  Please welcome Vanessa Marshall, the voice and the heart behind our favorite Twi'lek and Rebel revolutionary, Hera Sydulla.  Hera was introduced in Star Wars Rebels and continued her role in The Bad Batch and Forces of Destiny.

Vanessa was nominated for an Annie Award for Best Voice Acting in Studio Ghibli’s 2021 animated film Earwig and The Witch; Vanessa She is best known for playing Hera in Star Wars: Rebels, Wonder Woman in DC’s Harley Quinn, Gamora in Guardians of the Galaxy, Black Canary in Young Justice, and Ruth Bader Ginsberg in Rick and Morty. 

In the world of video games, she is Sheeva in Mortal Combat 11, Olga in Metal Gear Solid 2, and Jan Ors in Star Wars: Jedi Knights II.  As an avid gamer, she live streams regularly on her Twitch channel. She announces ABC, NBC, CBS, Fox, HGTV, VH1 and MTV TV promos. She narrates shows for ESPN, Lifetime, E!, TLC, and Tennis Channel. 

Raised in a show business family by Joan Van Ark of Knots Landing and John Marshall of KNBC News, her first acting job was with Julie Harris playing her mother’s role (Valene Ewing) as a child. Vanessa’s award-winning sculptures earned her admission into Princeton University. After acquiring a Masters in acting from NYU, she performed stand-up at The Comedy Store and The Improv and sketch comedy at the Acme Comedy Theater. 

Meet Vanessa at the Washington State Toy Show on April 1st and 2nd in Puyallup.  She will be with us on both days, meeting fans, signing autographs and taking photos at the show. Tickets are on sale at the box office on the days of the show.  www.watoyshow.com

So ready for Day 1 of @dreamhack Dallas! Come say hello at the Diablo booth (signing 10am-2pm), judging an art competition 3-4pm, and playing D&D 5:30-9:30pm on main stage! Let’s gooooo! 🙌🏻💯

Huge thanks to @cesdvoiceover @brittweiskopf88 @erinhucke for the opportunity to participate in such an amazing esports experience! Grateful to DREAM BIG! 🙏🏻🧡✨✨✨
Day 2 of @dreamhack Dallas! Can’t wait to moderate @sweeetanj “Staying Human” panel! Come say hello at the Diablo panel (signing 3-7pm today)! Ready for a great day! Xo 🧡🧡🧡

Had so much fun today moderating @sweeetanj panel “Staying Human: Being an Artist in the Age of Technology.” Fascinating discussion about parasocial relationships, the need for certain boundaries, and the far reaching impact various platforms have had on her vast career. So much wisdom and insight from my favorite human! She is a force of nature! 🙏🏻💕✨

Come join us tomorrow for panels: “Voices of Diablo” at 11am with @sweeetanj @jhalegram @robinatkindownes & “Voices of Halo” at 12:15pm with @robinatkindownes and Debra Wilson! We will be at Diablo booth afterwards, so come say hi! 🙏🏻❤️✨

STAR WARS REBELS’ VANESSA MARSHALL TO APPEAR AT THE NORTHERN NATIONAL

Vanessa Marshall will appear at the Northern National Collectors’ Convention at Caesars Windsor from September 29 to October 1, 2023. The event is presented by Brimstone Games and will feature the Cartoon Kingdom Fan Experience. 

Marshall is best known for her portrayals as Hera Syndulla (Star Wars Rebels), Wonder Woman (DC’s Harley Quinn), and Gamora (Marvel’s animated series Guardians of the Galaxy). She also portrayed Mary Jane Watson (The Spectacular Spider-Man), Lt. Ottessa Warren (Star Trek: Lower Decks) and Black Canary (Young Justice: Phantoms) to name a few.

In the world of gaming, Marshall has portrayed Sheeva and Sonya Blade in the Mortal Kombat series and is an avid gamer herself.

“I can’t wait to meet with fans at the Northern National,” says Marshall.

Marshall will appear at the convention Friday through Sunday; September 29-October 1, 2023. Autographs, selfies, and professional photo opportunities will be available for sale to fans. 

“We’re thrilled to welcome Vanessa Marshall to the convention this fall,” says Northern National President Jeremy Renaud.

Vanessa Marshall is presented by Cartoon Kingdom.

Grab your tickets to meet Obi-Wan Kenobi and Duchess Satine Kryze here👇
https://www.chattanoogacomiccon.com/event-details/

James Arnold Taylor is known for his versatile vocal range. From 11-year-old flame-headed Johnny Test, to Jedi Knights Obi-Wan Kenobi and Plo Koon, to prehistoric caveman Fred Flintstone, as well as starring roles in some of the most successful video game series of all time: Ratchet and Clank (Ratchet), and Final Fantasy X (Tidus). He’s played innumerable superheroes in film and television:Spider-Man, The Flash, Magneto, Green Arrow, Yondu, Robin, The Silver Surfer, and Leonardo the Ninja Turtle, to name a few. He voice-doubles for countless
celebrities including Johnny Depp, Michael J. Fox, Christopher Walken, Justin Timberlake, Christopher Lloyd, and David Spade. He has lent his voice to all five of the latest Star Wars films, as well as Lieutenant Bek in the Disney attraction Rise of the Resistance. You can hear James daily as the voice of Fox Sunday’s Animation Domination and can be seen on-camera in the documentaries “I Know that Voice” and “The Last Blockbuster”.

Anna Graves has been bringing characters to life through her voice for two decades, including in numerous fan-favorite video games, like the World of Warcraft series, Call of Duty series, Ratchet & Clank, Disney Infinity 3.0, Marvel Avengers, and dozens of others. She has also provided voices for major anime and animation properties, including Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles, Big Mouth, Voltron: Legendary Defender, Two and a Half Men, Star Wars Rebels, and famously, as fan-favorite Duchess Satine Kryze on Star Wars: The Clone Wars.

Today I wanted to share something incredibly cool that happened to Laurelyn for her birthday. A couple weeks ago, I posted a video of Laurelyn opening her birthday present, a bunch of new rare and even autographed trading cards of her absolute favorite @StarWars character, Hera Syndulla from #StarWarsRebels.

In that post I tagged Vanessa Marshall, who voices Hera in the show, not really expecting any sort of reply or acknowledgement. I was so thrilled when she ended up leaving a comment that I could show Laurelyn the next morning. She thought that was THE coolest thing...

She had NO idea that Vanessa had also reached out to me privately with a desire to send Laurelyn a little personalized happy birthday package.

@vanessamarshall1138 had no obligation to reply to or 'heart' my birthday post that I tagged her in. Yet she did.

And she *absolutely* had no obligation to contact me, get our address, sign a personalized photo, purchase a birthday card, personalize and sign that birthday card, also throwing in a handful of really cool Rebels themed stickers and trading cards. Yet she did...

My wife and I were already big fans. To be honest, Star Wars Rebels is some of my favorite #StarWars content period. Coming from me, that is extremely high praise. It really is that good. I adore the Ghost crew. 

But now, having given my daughter such an amazing and heartfelt birthday gift, Vanessa Marshall has risen from "one of my favorite voice actors" to simply "one of my favorite people" because she made my Little Miss feel like the most important girl in the galaxy for her birthday.

Thank you, General Syndulla. We have hope!

Happy New Years & welcome to our Operation Fandom 2024 Pop Culture Convention Event page. 
 
This years event will be held Sunday April 21st, 2024 from 10-5 w/ early bird entrance starting at 9am . 

 We will have lots to announce here throughout January as we finalize this years celebrity appearance lineup .  Here’s what we have for you so far 🎉

1. Vendors - Last year’s vendors will have first crack at this years event & can expect to be receiving this years vendors contract by email by this Sunday Jan 7. 
  We will then open up any remaining vendor spaces to the public after Sunday Jan 21, 2024.

2.  Our Cosplay contest is back & bigger than ever & will be featured on the main stage throughout the afternoon. Thanks to @rubbercitycosplay for again helping us with the contest .

3. We are excited to announce our 1st guest appearance for this years convention: 
VANESSA MARSHALL🙌🎉 @vanessamarshall1138 
 Vanessa is world renowned voice actor known for her many roles such as :
- Hera in Star Wars Rebels 
- Wonder Woman in DC’s Harley Quinn
- Gamora in Guardians of the Galaxy 
- Black Canary in Young Justice :Phantoms 
As well as voices in the video gaming world: 
- Sheeva in Mortal Kombat 11 
- Olga in Metal Gear Solid 2
- Jan Ors in Star Wars : Jedi Knights II 
+ so much more ! ( stay tuned for autograph & photo op pricing).
